"nun único ficheiro."

#. Tag: para
#: basics.docbook:526
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have created a new document, or want to save an existing one under a "
"different name, use <menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem> Save "
"As...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. This will bring up &kde;'s common "
"<guilabel>Save Document As</guilabel> dialog box. Choose the folder where "
"you want to save the document and enter a suitable file name into the "
"<guilabel>Name</guilabel> text box. &sheets; documents are normally "
"automatically saved with a <filename>.ods</filename> extension, you do not "
"need to add this to the filename but do make sure that the <guilabel>Filter</"
"guilabel> selection is set to <guilabel>OpenDocument SpreadSheet</guilabel>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: basics.docbook:536
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To save your document without changing its name, just use <menuchoice> "
"<guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Save</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Para gardar o seu documento sen cambiar o nome, use "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Ficheiro</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Gardar</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: basics.docbook:539
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "You can also save a &kspread; document in a foreign format: see the "
#| "Import/Export section for more information about doing this."
msgid ""
"You can also save a &sheets; document in a foreign format selecting the "
"format from the <guilabel>Filter:</guilabel> combo box."
